== Personal ==

=== Automobile accident ===

On October 13, 2009, Davies, who was in [[Washington, D.C.]] for a [[World Cup Qualifier]] game between [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], was a passenger in an [[Sports utility vehicle|SUV]] that went out of control on the [[George Washington Parkway]] and struck a metal railing at about 3:15 a.m., tearing the vehicle in half. The accident shut down the George Washington Parkway until 8:15 a.m. that morning. The accident killed a 22-year old woman who was in the car with Davies, while Davies himself suffered a lacerated [[Urinary bladder|bladder]], fractured right [[tibia]] and [[femur]], a fractured [[elbow]], and [[Facial trauma|facial]] injuries.<ref>{{Cite web |title=U.S. Men's National Team Forward Charlie Davies Out of Surgery and in Serious but Stable Condition |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Mens-National-Team/2009/10/US-Mens-National-Team-Forward-Charlie-Davies-Out-of-Surgery-and-in-Serious-buut-Stable-Condition.aspx |work=[[United States Soccer Federation]] |date=Oct. 13, 2009 |accessdate=December 8, 2009}}</ref><ref name="WashPost-accident">{{Cite news |first=Steven |last=Goff |title=Davies in Serious Accident |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/soccerinsider/2009/10/davies_in_serious_accident.html?wprss=soccerinsider |work=[[Washington Post]] |date=October 13, 2009 |accessdate=December 8, 2009}}</ref><ref name="soccernet-accident">{{Cite news |title=U.S. striker Davies injured in car accident |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story?id=685080&sec=us&cc=5901 |work=[[ESPNsoccernet]] |date=October 13, 2009 |accessdate=December 8, 2009}}</ref> In an interview with ESPN's [[Jeremy Schaap]] on December 4, Davies said that he expects to be running by March and will be fit to play at the World Cup.<ref>{{Cite podcast |url=http://search.espn.go.com/charlie-davies/audio/7<!-- Could not find a direct link because the interview is linked by a java script. --> |title=World Cup Preview Show |website=[[ESPN.com]] |host=[[Jeremy Schaap]] |date=December 04, 2009 |accessdate=December 08, 2009}}</ref> On January 25, 2010, [[ESPNsoccernet]] reported Davies is jogging and hopes to return to [[FC Sochaux-Montb<U+00E9>liard|Sochaux]] by April.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Ives |last=Galarcep |title=Davies on remarkable path to recovery |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/world-cup/story/_/id/4856256/ce/us/davies-remarkable-path-recovery?cc=3888&ver=global |work=ESPNsoccernet |date=February 2, 2010 |accessdate=February 19, 2010}}</ref> Davies returned to France to complete his rehabilitation with his club, Sochaux, on February 17, 2010, with plans to commence full team training within a month.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Davies says he's a month from resuming training |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2010/soccer/02/18/davies.injury.ap/index.html |work=Sports Illustrated |agency=Associated Press |date=February 18, 2010 |accessdate=February 19, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Exclusive video interview with Charlie Davies |url=http://www.fcsochaux.fr/en/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1431&Itemid=106 |publisher=FC Sochaux-Montb<U+00E9>liard |date=18 February 2010  |accessdate=February 19, 2010}}</ref> He resumed light training with the club on March 22.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Davies resumes training after accident |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2010/soccer/03/22/davies.ap/index.html |work=Sports Illustrated |agency=Associated Press |date=March 22, 2010 |accessdate=March 23, 2010}}</ref>

